* Add 3-parameter functions to <llapi/extended_user_functions.h>
* Attributes need a true 'any' kind and a true 'none' kind (type matching).
* Object Filters (in the new RT)
* Image Filters (in the new RT)
* RT needs some method of allowing multiple stack frames.
  Possibly something like this:
  enter(RETURN_NAME);   // enter a stack frame, storing the value
                        // returned upon leaving in the given (local)
                        // variable name.  

  ... Do junk...

  define  -- Affects *LOCAL* frame.
  redefine -- Affects frame where it is currently defined (if not
              defined, sets in local).

  defined -- checks all frames.

  ... End junk...

  leave(RETURN_VALUE);  // Place the return value given into the
                        // previous stack frame under the variable
                        // name given in the corresponding enter()
                        // call. 
* Consider replacing 'define', 'redefine', and 'defined' with functions
  instead of being internal (parser) constructs.  
* Consider adding a 'local' function, for defining a local variable
  capable of assignment using the ASSIGN operator.  If already visible
  in the local scope, or part of an attribute of a currently active
  object, a warning (or error) should be emitted.
